WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:05.797
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:27.152
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:41.750 --> 00:44.753
{\an8}<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

00:44.836 --> 00:50.717
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.800 --> 00:52.969
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:53.052 --> 00:53.970
{\an3}- [giggles]
Guys, guys!

00:54.053 --> 00:56.347
They messed up our taco order.

00:56.431 --> 00:58.808
{\an3}It was quadrupled!
[laughs]

00:58.892 --> 01:01.394
Let Taco-Palooza begin!

01:01.478 --> 01:03.062
- [grunts]

01:03.146 --> 01:06.566
{\an1}- Who says you can't have Taco
Thursday on a Friday, huh?

01:06.649 --> 01:07.817
'Cause I'm gonna get that guy.

01:07.901 --> 01:09.986
all: Pig Goat Banana Cricket

01:10.069 --> 01:12.781
Taco Thursday
on a Friday high-five.

01:14.032 --> 01:16.284
- [giggles]

01:16.367 --> 01:18.703
Hey, get a load
of this taco wrapper ad.

01:18.787 --> 01:21.206
The Banana Bunch
are having a show tonight

01:21.289 --> 01:22.916
at the Stink Pavilion.

01:22.999 --> 01:24.626
And they're doing it without me?

01:24.709 --> 01:25.877
- Without you?
- [burps]

01:25.960 --> 01:27.462
What do you mean, bro-nana?

01:27.545 --> 01:29.380
- Didn't I ever tell you guys?
I used to be part of

01:29.464 --> 01:31.674
an internationally famous
singing group with my family:

01:31.758 --> 01:33.676
The Banana Bunch.
- [grunts]

01:33.760 --> 01:35.887
Wait, I remember
the Banana Bunch.

01:35.970 --> 01:38.556
That was you?
- Yeah, didn't they sing

01:38.640 --> 01:40.183
"More Than a Peeling"?

01:40.266 --> 01:42.811
- That was just one
of our hokey, humdrum hits.

01:42.894 --> 01:45.188
Check it out.
We topped all the charts,

01:45.271 --> 01:46.689
graced magazine covers.

01:46.773 --> 01:48.942
<i>We were it until--</i>

01:49.025 --> 01:50.527
<i>it was 39 years ago,</i>

01:50.610 --> 01:53.279
<i>we were playing our biggest,</i>
<i>sold out show yet,</i>

01:53.363 --> 01:55.198
<i>and I was bored of</i>
<i>the "same old same old,"</i>

01:55.281 --> 01:58.743
<i>so I decided to try something</i>
<i>just a little bit different.</i>

01:58.827 --> 02:00.078
[wacky music]

02:00.161 --> 02:01.079
all: ♪ When you make a mess ♪

02:01.162 --> 02:03.540
♪ Clean it up
with no protest ♪

02:03.623 --> 02:06.835
♪ Pick your socks up
off the floor ♪

02:06.918 --> 02:10.713
♪ And when you sleep
try not to snore... ♪

02:10.797 --> 02:12.882
- [grunts]
Ah!

02:12.966 --> 02:14.843
[rock music]
- ♪ The future is grimy ♪

02:14.926 --> 02:16.719
♪ The future is slimy ♪

02:16.803 --> 02:18.388
♪ Barf on my computer ♪

02:18.471 --> 02:20.598
♪ Not my motor scooter ♪

02:20.682 --> 02:22.225
[crowd screaming]

02:22.308 --> 02:24.978
Yeah, ooh-ooh, ah!

02:25.061 --> 02:27.146
[all screaming]

02:32.235 --> 02:34.362
- Look what you did,
you goofy turkey!

02:34.445 --> 02:35.572
Get out of here!

02:35.655 --> 02:36.656
- [breathing heavily]

02:36.739 --> 02:39.909
{\an3}[sobbing]

02:39.993 --> 02:42.245
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:42.328 --> 02:43.580
{\an3}- Wow.

02:43.663 --> 02:45.123
- [crying]

02:45.206 --> 02:47.584
I-I wish I could play
with the band one more time.

02:47.667 --> 02:49.502
{\an3}- Why don't you?
I'm sure they've forgotten

02:49.586 --> 02:53.214
{\an3}about the world's greatest
show biz disaster.

02:53.298 --> 02:55.925
{\an1}- And even if your dad
still remembers,

02:56.009 --> 02:58.177
{\an1}he's got to have
forgiven you by now.

02:58.261 --> 03:00.972
{\an1}You were just a tiny,
itty-bitty misguided fruit.

03:01.055 --> 03:02.223
- [sniffles]

03:02.307 --> 03:04.475
You--you know what?
You're right!

03:04.559 --> 03:06.394
I'm heading over there
right now.

03:06.477 --> 03:08.771
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

03:08.855 --> 03:11.691
[overlapping vocalizing]

03:11.774 --> 03:15.028
- Uh, hey--hey, guys.
I'm back.

03:15.111 --> 03:16.529
all: Banana!
- Hey, there.

03:16.613 --> 03:18.448
- Oh, it's been a long time,
son.

03:18.531 --> 03:20.366
{\an1}- I see the old band is doing
a reunion concert.

03:20.450 --> 03:24.329
{\an1}I was wondering if you--
maybe I could join you guys?

03:24.412 --> 03:25.622
- I think that's
a wonderful idea.

03:25.705 --> 03:26.789
- Oh, terrific.
- Why not?

03:26.873 --> 03:29.125
- What?
That's a terrible idea.

03:29.208 --> 03:32.211
- But, dear, he's our son.

03:32.295 --> 03:33.630
- I don't care.

03:33.713 --> 03:35.715
If you're here to beg
to rejoin the group,

03:35.798 --> 03:37.842
start begging,

03:37.926 --> 03:39.552
and then the answer is "no"!

03:39.636 --> 03:41.137
- I know when I'm not wanted.

03:41.220 --> 03:42.305
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:42.388 --> 03:43.932
{\an1}You're still
the bitter curmudgeon

03:44.015 --> 03:45.391
I remember.

03:45.475 --> 03:46.726
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:46.809 --> 03:49.228
- [grunts]

03:49.312 --> 03:51.731
[groans]

03:51.814 --> 03:54.901
[sobbing]

03:54.984 --> 03:57.904
{\an3}- Banana, there's something
we need to tell you.

03:57.987 --> 03:59.197
{\an3}- Uh, yeah.

03:59.280 --> 04:01.199
- That Dad is
never gonna forgive me?

04:01.282 --> 04:02.742
- That's true,
but, no.

04:02.825 --> 04:06.204
{\an3}- The reason Dad is even more of
a jerk than usual is...

04:06.287 --> 04:07.288
- Wh--what?

04:07.372 --> 04:08.414
- He has...

04:08.498 --> 04:09.415
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:09.499 --> 04:11.334
- Mushy spots.

04:11.417 --> 04:13.878
- What?
Dad has the mush?

04:13.962 --> 04:15.171
- [gasps]

04:15.254 --> 04:16.339
{\an3}Uh...
[grunts]

04:16.422 --> 04:20.551
- Yeah, pretty soon
he'll be inedible.

04:20.635 --> 04:23.596
- This could be his last show.
- Last show?

04:23.680 --> 04:25.848
{\an7}- He might not even make it
through the show tonight.

04:25.932 --> 04:27.141
{\an8}- We need you, Banana.

04:27.225 --> 04:29.644
{\an9}You gotta come.
Please!

04:29.727 --> 04:31.521
[indistinct chatter]

04:31.604 --> 04:32.814
[cheers and applause]

04:32.897 --> 04:34.023
all: ♪ Milk and honey ♪

04:34.107 --> 04:35.817
- [coughing]
all: ♪ Make for sweet kisses ♪

04:35.900 --> 04:37.986
♪ If you don't believe me ♪

04:38.069 --> 04:39.654
♪ Just ask the Mrs. ♪
- ♪ Just ask-- ♪

04:39.737 --> 04:41.364
[babbles]
- It's true.

04:41.447 --> 04:44.617
[off-key singing]
- [coughing continues]

04:44.701 --> 04:47.328
[singing gibberish]

04:47.412 --> 04:50.498
[booing and shouting]

04:52.750 --> 04:55.294
[coughing]
all: Dad!

04:56.504 --> 04:59.048
- Oh, man,
they're dying up there.

04:59.132 --> 05:00.133
- [grunts]

05:00.216 --> 05:02.719
My mushy spots.
[exhales]

05:02.802 --> 05:05.513
- Your arm.
- I know it's my arm.

05:05.596 --> 05:07.098
It's my arm!

05:07.181 --> 05:09.726
- Dad's mush,
it's worse than ever.

05:09.809 --> 05:11.144
- It's my mush.

05:11.227 --> 05:12.562
N--now get out of here.

05:12.645 --> 05:14.981
Beat it.
Scram!

05:15.064 --> 05:16.858
- Not this time, Dad.

05:16.941 --> 05:18.067
[crowd shouting]

05:18.151 --> 05:20.445
all: Banana, what're you doing?

05:20.528 --> 05:21.738
- Don't worry, guys.

05:21.821 --> 05:25.074
Boopelite, get ready to rock!

05:25.158 --> 05:26.659
{\an8}"Change family."

05:26.743 --> 05:29.203
Okay, guys, let's glam you up.

05:29.287 --> 05:30.913
[energy crackles]

05:30.997 --> 05:32.540
[all shout and groan]

05:32.623 --> 05:34.834
[rock music]

05:34.917 --> 05:37.545
♪ ♪

05:37.628 --> 05:39.464
♪ The future is grimy ♪

05:39.547 --> 05:41.215
♪ The future is slimy ♪

05:41.299 --> 05:42.258
both: ♪ Barf on my computer ♪

05:42.341 --> 05:46.971
all: ♪ Not my motor scooter ♪

05:47.055 --> 05:49.390
[cheers and applause]

05:49.474 --> 05:51.476
- I don't wanna hear
that garbage.

05:51.559 --> 05:53.561
- This garbage
is gonna save your life.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.774
[energy crackles]

05:57.857 --> 05:59.442
- [screams]

05:59.525 --> 06:01.319
- [gasps]
Where's my husband?

06:01.402 --> 06:01.903
You vaporized him!

06:01.986 --> 06:04.947
- Ah, I did?

06:05.031 --> 06:07.950
[saxophone rock music]

06:08.034 --> 06:09.327
[crowd roars]

06:09.410 --> 06:09.786
- [gasps]

06:09.869 --> 06:12.455
♪ ♪

06:12.538 --> 06:14.290
[cheers and applause]

06:14.373 --> 06:16.459
{\an1}- I'm back!
My mushy spots are gone!

06:16.542 --> 06:19.962
{\an1}You were right.
Glam rock saved my life,

06:20.046 --> 06:21.506
and the Banana Bunch.

06:21.589 --> 06:22.173
- I love you, Dad.

06:22.256 --> 06:25.301
- Shut up and rock, son.

06:25.384 --> 06:28.304
[rock music]

06:28.387 --> 06:32.225
♪ ♪

06:33.601 --> 06:34.310
- [barking]

06:34.393 --> 06:36.979
{\an8}[panting]
- [humming]

06:37.063 --> 06:38.272
{\an8}[kissing]
Hmm.

06:38.356 --> 06:39.941
{\an8}- Hi, Angry Old Raisin.
- [growls softly]

06:40.024 --> 06:41.692
{\an8}Guess who's here?
- [grunts]

06:41.776 --> 06:43.319
- It's me, Pig.

06:43.402 --> 06:46.197
{\an3}You don't have to guess.
You win.

06:46.280 --> 06:47.949
- What do I win?
- A big hug

06:48.032 --> 06:50.868
{\an3}from your fourth best friend
in the whole wide world.

06:50.952 --> 06:53.287
Aww.
- I don't wanna win a hug.

06:53.371 --> 06:55.289
I wanna win Dog-a-Palooza.

06:55.373 --> 06:57.583
Boopelite's premiere dog show.

06:57.667 --> 06:59.043
{\an3}- [gasps]
You're a dog?

06:59.127 --> 07:01.838
I knew it.
- I'm not a dog, you dope.

07:01.921 --> 07:05.174
{\an3}My dog,
Kimmel Fritz, is gonna win.

07:05.258 --> 07:08.344
{\an3}We've been training for this day
for 39 years.

07:08.427 --> 07:09.470
- [barks]

07:09.554 --> 07:10.888
- We're gonna beat the fuzz

07:10.972 --> 07:13.891
off of Owl Woman Lady
and her dog, Trumpet.

07:13.975 --> 07:17.145
They always win,
but not this year.

07:17.228 --> 07:18.855
Now go away.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.439
I'm gonna grab my pooper scooper

07:20.523 --> 07:22.608
and we're off
to win first prize.

07:22.692 --> 07:24.360
[door closes]
- Hey, Kimmel Fritz.

07:24.443 --> 07:26.362
Who's a cute little poochie?

07:26.445 --> 07:27.697
Yeah, you are.

07:27.780 --> 07:29.282
Hey, let's play fetch.

07:29.365 --> 07:30.908
Oh, oh, ready?
- [barking]

07:30.992 --> 07:32.243
- And go get it!

07:32.326 --> 07:34.203
[echoing dog barks,
air whistling]

07:39.750 --> 07:42.753
Oh, no, he's gone.

07:42.837 --> 07:44.839
Angry Old Raisin
can't win the dog show

07:44.922 --> 07:46.007
without his dog.

07:46.090 --> 07:47.550
What am I gonna do?

07:47.633 --> 07:49.177
Think, Pig, think.

07:49.260 --> 07:50.261
[bell dings]

07:50.344 --> 07:51.220
[wind whipping]

07:51.304 --> 07:52.847
<i>[victorious music]</i>

07:54.891 --> 07:56.309
- Okay, Kimmel Fritz,

07:56.392 --> 07:59.270
let's go win the pants
off of this dog show.

07:59.353 --> 08:01.480
Where the heck are you, hmm?

08:01.564 --> 08:04.400
- Arf, arf.
- [grunts]

08:04.483 --> 08:07.278
{\an3}[gnawing]

08:08.279 --> 08:09.572
- My glasses.

08:09.655 --> 08:10.698
I can barely see without them.

08:10.781 --> 08:14.785
{\an1}You must be really excited
to win Dog-a-Palooza.

08:14.869 --> 08:16.746
{\an3}- I am.
I mean, bark.

08:16.829 --> 08:18.497
- You feeling okay, Buster?

08:18.581 --> 08:19.749
- [poorly mimics dog barking]

08:19.832 --> 08:21.751
{\an3}Mm...
[poorly mimics dog barking]

08:21.834 --> 08:24.629
{\an1}- You're right, Kimmel Fritz.
You'll be my eyes.

08:24.712 --> 08:27.340
Now, let's win this thing.

08:27.423 --> 08:29.175
[dogs barking]

08:29.258 --> 08:32.303
- Ladies, gentlemen,

08:32.385 --> 08:35.597
welcome to Dog-a-Palooza.

08:35.681 --> 08:39.434
Now, let us get down
and doggity with it.

08:39.519 --> 08:43.231
{\an3}- Kimmel Fritz,
ah, we're gonna win this year.

08:43.313 --> 08:44.982
I just know it!

08:45.066 --> 08:47.985
{\an3}- Hardly.
My dog, Trumpet, and I...

08:48.069 --> 08:49.820
- [barks]
- Are going to beat

08:49.904 --> 08:52.615
the Bea Arthur out of you
and your mangy mutt.

08:52.698 --> 08:55.159
Just like we do every year.

08:55.243 --> 08:58.079
[laughs and hoots]

08:58.704 --> 09:02.041
Come on!
Come on!

09:02.124 --> 09:04.961
- [grunting]

09:05.044 --> 09:10.383
- That is the most hideous dog
that I have ever seen.

09:10.466 --> 09:12.468
- What?
He's the best dog

09:12.551 --> 09:14.136
in the entire world.
- [growling]

09:14.220 --> 09:17.348
{\an3}- Now get out of my way,
you goofy chicken.

09:17.431 --> 09:18.891
I got a dog show to win.

09:18.975 --> 09:23.437
{\an1}- We begin with the Trot
and Prance Obstacle Course.

09:23.521 --> 09:24.563
- It's on.

09:24.647 --> 09:27.316
- Like the break of dawn.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.484
[humming]

09:28.567 --> 09:30.903
<i>[lilting music]</i>

09:30.987 --> 09:33.990
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

09:34.073 --> 09:37.785
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:37.868 --> 09:39.287
- A butterfly pickle?

09:39.370 --> 09:43.374
Yum!
- [grunting]

09:43.457 --> 09:45.334
- [groaning]

09:45.418 --> 09:46.627
Stop!

09:46.711 --> 09:49.672
- [grunting]

09:49.755 --> 09:53.050
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

09:53.134 --> 09:54.677
- How dare you!

09:54.760 --> 09:56.804
- For the love of Mike!

09:56.887 --> 09:59.974
[all shouting and grunting]

10:00.850 --> 10:02.727
- Help.
- [grunting, farts]

10:04.770 --> 10:07.523
- And now for
the novel writing portion

10:07.606 --> 10:09.191
of the competition.

10:09.275 --> 10:12.069
{\an3}Dogs, ready.
Set.

10:12.153 --> 10:15.531
Typewrite!

10:15.615 --> 10:17.575
[keys clacking,
typewriters dinging]

10:17.658 --> 10:20.661
- Mm...
[grumbling, grunting]

10:20.745 --> 10:23.414
<i>[lilting music]</i>

10:23.497 --> 10:26.042
[gnawing]

10:26.125 --> 10:27.752
[typewriter dings]
[gurgles]

10:27.835 --> 10:30.046
- And for
the final competition...

10:30.129 --> 10:32.465
{\an1}[giggles]
My personal favorite,

10:32.548 --> 10:34.967
{\an1}swim wear!
[giggles]

10:35.051 --> 10:36.052
[rock music playing]

10:36.135 --> 10:39.055
[applause]

10:39.138 --> 10:41.390
♪ ♪

10:41.474 --> 10:43.392
[cheers and applause]

10:43.476 --> 10:45.478
- [murmurs]

10:45.561 --> 10:47.063
[cheers and applause
intensifies]

10:47.146 --> 10:48.481
{\an3}[humming]

10:48.564 --> 10:51.150
{\an3}[shouting]

10:52.485 --> 10:53.235
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:53.319 --> 10:56.197
- Help me!

10:56.280 --> 10:58.157
- [trumpets]

11:00.409 --> 11:01.869
- [grunts]
- How dare you!

11:01.952 --> 11:05.748
You and your mangy dog
have ruined everything!

11:05.831 --> 11:07.083
- [grunting]

11:07.166 --> 11:08.626
- Hey, you can't speak
to my fourth best friend

11:08.709 --> 11:11.379
in the whole wide world
like that!

11:11.462 --> 11:14.799
I mean...bark?

11:14.882 --> 11:16.300
crowd: [gasp]

11:16.384 --> 11:18.928
{\an3}- You're not a dog.
You're a pig.

11:19.011 --> 11:21.931
{\an3}This is grounds
for immediate disqualification.

11:22.014 --> 11:23.432
- What in the hoot?

11:23.516 --> 11:25.142
- You're not my Kimmel Fritz.

11:25.226 --> 11:27.311
- I know.
It's me.

11:27.395 --> 11:30.064
[belches, gags]

11:31.440 --> 11:32.733
{\an1}- Pig!

11:32.817 --> 11:33.401
- I'm sorry, Angry Old Raisin,

11:33.484 --> 11:35.820
but I lost your dog

11:35.903 --> 11:38.197
and didn't want you
to lose Dog-a-Palooza, again.

11:38.280 --> 11:41.450
{\an3}- [laughs, hoots]
You're a loser.

11:41.534 --> 11:42.284
[gerbils squeaking]

11:42.368 --> 11:44.328
crowd: [gasps]

11:44.412 --> 11:47.623
{\an3}- A dog impersonated
by ten gerbils?

11:47.706 --> 11:49.458
{\an1}In all my years,
I have never seen a dog

11:49.542 --> 11:52.294
impersonated by ten gerbils.

11:52.378 --> 11:54.630
You're disqualified too!

11:54.713 --> 11:56.549
{\an1}- [laughs]
Hoot, hoot, hoot, yourself.

11:56.632 --> 11:59.301
- But if we're disqualified,
who wins?

11:59.385 --> 12:01.804
- I do!
- What?

12:01.887 --> 12:02.555
- No way!
- [barks]

12:02.638 --> 12:05.057
- Ah!
- Kimmel Fritz!

12:05.141 --> 12:06.308
{\an1}- Amazing.

12:06.392 --> 12:08.978
{\an1}This dog perfectly impersonated
a judge.

12:09.061 --> 12:12.606
{\an1}[giggles]
I award you first place.

12:12.690 --> 12:13.858
- We finally win!

12:13.941 --> 12:16.444
I'm old, but happy!

12:16.527 --> 12:17.820
- How dare they!

12:17.903 --> 12:20.156
Hoot, hoot, hoot, hoot.
- You're welcome,

12:20.239 --> 12:23.242
{\an3}fourth best friend
in the whole wide world.

12:23.325 --> 12:24.785
[gasps, pants]

12:24.869 --> 12:26.287
- Fetch, Pig.
- [babbles]

12:26.370 --> 12:27.663
[car horn honking, tires squeal]
- [screams]

12:27.746 --> 12:28.956
[crash]
- [laughs]

12:29.039 --> 12:30.124
I didn't even throw it.

12:32.668 --> 12:34.170
- [humming]

12:34.253 --> 12:36.630
Aw, my horns are all fajangled.

12:36.714 --> 12:38.841
[buffer whirring]

12:38.924 --> 12:41.260
[buffer grinds,
electricity crackles]

12:41.343 --> 12:42.595
Huh?
Oh, no.

12:42.678 --> 12:44.930
My best beloved buffer
just biffed it.

12:45.014 --> 12:48.017
Ah, I love this buffer.

12:48.100 --> 12:50.853
Hi, operator?
I have a horn buffer emergency.

12:50.936 --> 12:53.647
[door bell rings]
Wow, that was fast.

12:54.982 --> 12:57.902
<i>[upbeat romantic music]</i>
<i>- ♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

12:57.985 --> 12:59.278
- Towel-o there.

12:59.361 --> 13:00.863
Did somebody call Tony Towel,

13:00.946 --> 13:03.032
the world's
number one repair man?

13:03.115 --> 13:04.867
<i>[horns sounds]</i>
- [babbles]

13:04.950 --> 13:07.578
[breathing heavily]
[babbles]

13:07.661 --> 13:09.788
{\an1}I dith.
I'm Goath...

13:09.872 --> 13:12.625
{\an1}[chuckles]
Excuse me a moment.

13:12.708 --> 13:14.793
{\an1}[chuckles]
I'm sorry about that.

13:14.877 --> 13:15.878
Hi, I'm Goat,

13:15.961 --> 13:17.379
{\an1}and I'm very pleased
to love you--

13:17.463 --> 13:19.465
{\an1}[laughs]
I mean, marry you--

13:19.548 --> 13:20.758
I mean, meet you!

13:20.841 --> 13:21.926
{\an3}- Whoo-ah!

13:22.009 --> 13:25.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>
<i>- Oh, yeah.</i>

13:25.137 --> 13:26.597
{\an1}- Swoon.

13:26.680 --> 13:28.641
{\an3}- What seems to be the trouble,
Mrs. Goat?

13:28.724 --> 13:32.102
{\an1}- Oh, it's just Ms. Goat.
I'm single.

13:32.186 --> 13:33.896
There's no mister
with this sister.

13:33.979 --> 13:35.356
At least not yet, anyway.

13:35.439 --> 13:38.067
- So what needs repairing?
- My favorite buffer.

13:38.150 --> 13:40.152
{\an1}Moments ago,
it just stopped working.

13:40.236 --> 13:41.737
- Let me take a look.

13:41.820 --> 13:43.906
- What a stud.
- What's that?

13:43.989 --> 13:46.951
{\an1}- I mean, what a dud
this horn buffer is, stud.

13:47.034 --> 13:49.912
Oh, uh, so you think that it's
lovable--I me--I mean, fixable?

13:49.995 --> 13:53.082
{\an3}- Tony Towel can fix
the Bea Arthur out of anything.

13:53.165 --> 13:56.085
{\an3}Stand back.
Shi-ka!

13:56.168 --> 13:57.545
And that's towel I do it.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.296
[buffer whirring]
- Oh, wow, Tony.

13:59.380 --> 14:01.465
It is like new again.
Thanks.

14:01.549 --> 14:04.260
{\an3}- Welp, that'll do it,
Goat woman.

14:04.343 --> 14:05.970
- Wait!
Are you leaving so soon?

14:06.053 --> 14:08.138
{\an1}Be--because you just--
you just got here.

14:08.222 --> 14:10.891
{\an3}- Sorry, unless there's
something that needs a toweling,

14:10.975 --> 14:12.434
I ain't a-staying.

14:12.518 --> 14:14.395
- [grunting]

14:14.478 --> 14:16.230
<i>[quirky music]</i>

14:16.313 --> 14:17.398
- Interesting.

14:17.481 --> 14:19.275
Shi-ka, shi-ka, shi-ka!

14:19.358 --> 14:20.442
<i>[lilting musical flourish]</i>

14:20.526 --> 14:22.736
{\an1}And that's towel we do it.
Booya.

14:22.820 --> 14:24.113
- Wait, Tony.

14:24.196 --> 14:25.990
{\an3}I thought of something else
that needs fixing.

14:26.073 --> 14:27.408
{\an3}Follow me.

14:27.491 --> 14:31.120
{\an1}- Whoa, this room is
towel-y awesome.

14:31.203 --> 14:32.663
{\an3}- Anywho...

14:32.746 --> 14:35.958
{\an3}uh, my interdimensional portal
contraption thingy broke.

14:36.041 --> 14:38.794
{\an3}[chuckles]
Maybe you can fix it.

14:38.877 --> 14:41.797
{\an3}- It's gonna take
a really big towel movement

14:41.880 --> 14:42.923
to fix this one.

14:43.007 --> 14:45.175
[air whistling]

14:45.259 --> 14:46.552
Shi-ka!

14:46.635 --> 14:49.597
[rumbling, whirring]

14:49.680 --> 14:52.641
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:52.725 --> 14:55.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:55.394 --> 14:57.229
{\an3}There's nothing
Tony Towel can't fix

14:57.313 --> 14:59.023
with his amazing towel talents.

14:59.106 --> 15:01.442
Now, how 'bout some sugar?
<i>[bell dings]</i>

15:01.525 --> 15:03.235
{\an1}- Finally.

15:03.319 --> 15:05.112
- I mean some real sugar.
All this fixing

15:05.195 --> 15:08.407
{\an1}is making me feel weak
and low energy.

15:08.490 --> 15:09.825
{\an1}- Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
I knew that.

15:09.908 --> 15:11.201
{\an1}[chuckles]
I did.

15:11.285 --> 15:12.494
I really--I did.

15:12.578 --> 15:14.538
[both scream]
- Yum.

15:14.622 --> 15:17.750
{\an3}Fresh towel.
[laughs evilly]

15:17.833 --> 15:19.918
- [screams]

15:20.002 --> 15:21.337
- Oh, no, Tony!

15:21.420 --> 15:23.422
{\an1}This is kinda
a little bit my fault.

15:23.505 --> 15:25.966
{\an1}It's up to you, Goat,
to save Tony.

15:26.050 --> 15:27.051
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:27.134 --> 15:29.178
[screaming]

15:29.261 --> 15:33.682
Hey, troll face,
let go of my repairman or else.

15:33.766 --> 15:37.269
- [chuckles]
Or else what?

15:37.353 --> 15:39.980
[laughs evilly]
- Or else this.

15:40.064 --> 15:42.274
Shi-ka!
- [burps]

15:42.358 --> 15:43.776
- [breathing heavily]

15:43.859 --> 15:46.654
{\an1}- Thanks for saving Tony Towel's
totally terrific life.

15:46.737 --> 15:49.156
{\an3}- [laughs]
I would do anything for you.

15:49.239 --> 15:50.616
- Oh, yeah, that reminds me.

15:50.699 --> 15:54.703
{\an3}- OM-jeepers.
He's giving me his phone number?

15:54.787 --> 15:56.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:56.622 --> 15:59.041
{\an3}Hey, this isn't
your phone number!

15:59.124 --> 16:00.542
This is a bill.

16:00.626 --> 16:03.837
{\an1}- Yeah, I gave you my standard
10% discount for saving my life.

16:03.921 --> 16:05.047
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:05.130 --> 16:06.674
- [roars]

16:06.757 --> 16:08.759
- [grunting and shouting]

16:08.842 --> 16:10.886
- [grunting, breathing heavily]

16:10.969 --> 16:13.931
- Hm, I don't remember
leaving that on.

16:14.014 --> 16:16.016
Oh, well.

16:16.100 --> 16:17.893
[both grunt]

16:17.976 --> 16:19.269
[both scream]
- [roars]

16:20.270 --> 16:22.272
- Burgerstein, today is the day

16:22.356 --> 16:24.149
my hero Dr. Eggplant Face

16:24.233 --> 16:25.442
lets me into his...

16:25.526 --> 16:28.487
{\an3}[whispers]
Super Secret Science Society.

16:28.570 --> 16:29.697
How, you ask?

16:29.780 --> 16:32.074
- [grunts]
- [laughs]

16:32.157 --> 16:33.909
Oh, you couldn't be more wrong.

16:33.992 --> 16:36.412
{\an3}He's going to let me in
because of this.

16:36.495 --> 16:38.747
Presenting Smart Guy Spray.

16:38.831 --> 16:39.915
{\an3}Yes.

16:39.998 --> 16:42.418
{\an3}One spritz
of this tantalizing elixir

16:42.501 --> 16:44.878
will turn anyone into a genius.

16:44.962 --> 16:47.256
Even you.
- [grunts]

16:47.339 --> 16:49.216
[babbles]

16:49.299 --> 16:50.926
{\an3}- There.
How do you feel?

16:51.009 --> 16:54.680
- Ah, my little green companion.

16:54.763 --> 16:57.599
{\an1}I feel spectacular
and brilliant.

16:57.683 --> 16:59.435
{\an3}- [chitters]
Ooh, it worked!

16:59.518 --> 17:01.895
{\an3}It worked!
You talked all smart and stuff!

17:01.979 --> 17:04.565
{\an1}- You're miraculous concoction
will no doubt

17:04.647 --> 17:06.442
grant you access into the...

17:06.525 --> 17:09.069
{\an1}[whispers]
Super Secret Science Society.

17:09.153 --> 17:10.612
Congratulations!

17:10.695 --> 17:13.323
{\an3}- Yeah, I know, I know!
I'm a genius!

17:13.406 --> 17:15.117
Up top!
- Okay then.

17:15.200 --> 17:17.453
[grunts, babbles]

17:17.536 --> 17:21.123
{\an3}- [gasps] The Smart Guy Spray's
effects are only temporary.

17:21.205 --> 17:22.540
Oh, well, no worries.

17:22.624 --> 17:24.667
{\an3}I'll just give you
a couple extra spritzes

17:24.752 --> 17:27.171
{\an3}when Dr. Eggplant Face
gets here.

17:27.253 --> 17:28.839
- [grunts]

17:28.922 --> 17:31.425
I rang the bell.
I knocked.

17:31.508 --> 17:33.552
I'm not some front-porch freak

17:33.635 --> 17:36.138
you can just leave
out on your front porch.

17:36.221 --> 17:38.682
{\an3}- Oh, I'm so sorry,
Dr. Eggplant Face, sir.

17:38.766 --> 17:40.809
I-I guess I didn't
hear you knocking.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.144
[laughs nervously, murmurs]

17:42.227 --> 17:44.897
{\an1}- Cricket,
if you want to get into...

17:44.980 --> 17:48.150
{\an1}[whispers] The Super Secret
Science Society,

17:48.233 --> 17:52.529
{\an1}you'd better show me
something brilliant immediately.

17:52.613 --> 17:56.074
{\an1}- Presenting my assistant,
Burgerstein.

17:56.158 --> 17:57.326
As you can see,

17:57.409 --> 18:00.245
{\an1}he's just a 1/4 pounder of meat
for brains.

18:00.329 --> 18:01.955
- [babbles]
- Blah.

18:02.039 --> 18:05.501
{\an1}- Mm-hmm, but now
with just a few spritzes

18:05.584 --> 18:07.961
from my Smart Guy Spray...
- Ahh...

18:08.045 --> 18:10.005
- [humming]

18:10.088 --> 18:12.508
[electricity crackles]

18:12.591 --> 18:13.967
<i>[brain beating]</i>

18:14.051 --> 18:16.178
- "Things are as they are

18:16.261 --> 18:18.514
because they were as they were."

18:18.597 --> 18:20.349
Astrophysicist...

18:20.432 --> 18:22.142
both: Thomas Gold.

18:22.226 --> 18:24.019
- Mm.
- Quick, Burgerstein,

18:24.102 --> 18:27.105
{\an3}what's Einstein's
mass-energy equivalence?

18:29.566 --> 18:31.193
[grunts]

18:31.276 --> 18:33.278
- Oh, is he getting dumb again?

18:33.362 --> 18:35.072
- No, that was just some gas.

18:35.155 --> 18:38.033
{\an3}What he meant to say was...
[hums]

18:39.326 --> 18:41.870
[thrumming, squishing]

18:41.954 --> 18:43.872
[electricity crackles, erupts]

18:43.956 --> 18:46.875
- Nonetheless,
the scientific method mandates

18:46.959 --> 18:50.003
we repeatedly test and confirm
through experimentation.

18:50.087 --> 18:53.090
That's why I have invented this.

18:53.173 --> 18:55.050
- Mmm, that was fast.

18:55.134 --> 18:56.385
<i>[trilling whimsical music]</i>

18:56.468 --> 19:00.347
{\an1}- I've never seen anything
quite like it.

19:00.430 --> 19:04.059
{\an3}I hereby grant you admission
into the...

19:04.143 --> 19:07.312
{\an3}[whispers]
Super Secret Science Society.

19:07.396 --> 19:10.232
{\an1}- But I wanna be in the
Super Secret Science Society.

19:10.315 --> 19:13.902
{\an3}- Maybe one day,
you goofy chicken.

19:13.986 --> 19:15.028
{\an1}- [laughs]

19:15.112 --> 19:17.865
[both laughing]

19:17.948 --> 19:20.200
{\an1}- Thank you for the invitation,
Doctor,

19:20.284 --> 19:23.912
{\an1}but I've got much more
important matters to tend to.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.998
{\an1}- [grunts]
Like what?

19:26.081 --> 19:29.418
- Like taking over
the entire world!

19:29.501 --> 19:31.920
[laughs evilly]
[thunder crashes]

19:32.004 --> 19:34.381
That is, right after
I turn the two of you

19:34.464 --> 19:37.593
into Eggplant Parmesan
topped with Cricket sauce.

19:37.676 --> 19:38.802
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:38.886 --> 19:40.470
- Hey, wha--
- [gasps]

19:40.554 --> 19:42.472
- Way to go, Cricket.

19:42.556 --> 19:45.893
{\an3}All that smart spray of yours
has turned him into

19:45.976 --> 19:48.353
a totally evil scientist.

19:48.437 --> 19:50.606
{\an1}- Are you impressed?
Little bit?

19:50.689 --> 19:52.608
{\an3}- No.

19:52.691 --> 19:54.610
- Let's get cooking.

19:54.693 --> 19:56.403
[beeps]

19:56.486 --> 19:57.779
- [grunts, babbles]

19:57.863 --> 20:00.407
{\an1}Those pickle chips are
the source of his brain power.

20:00.490 --> 20:03.243
If only there was someone
who loved pickles so much

20:03.327 --> 20:05.245
that they would have
no problem consuming

20:05.329 --> 20:08.206
enormous radioactive pickles.

20:08.290 --> 20:09.583
- Hello.

20:09.666 --> 20:12.502
Burgerstein, did you
do something new with your bun?

20:12.586 --> 20:14.463
'Cause looking good.

20:14.546 --> 20:17.132
- Pig, he's going to eat us
and then take over the world!

20:17.215 --> 20:19.718
{\an1}- He's right, Pig.
So you're either against me

20:19.801 --> 20:23.305
{\an1}or you can join my plot
for world domination.

20:23.388 --> 20:24.556
- World domination?

20:24.640 --> 20:27.225
That's my favorite!
I'm in.

20:27.309 --> 20:28.810
- Pig, come on!

20:28.894 --> 20:31.521
- Right after I eat
those delicious pickles.

20:31.605 --> 20:33.190
[gnawing]

20:33.273 --> 20:34.983
{\an3}Yum.

20:35.067 --> 20:36.318
[powers down]

20:36.401 --> 20:38.403
- [babbles]

20:38.487 --> 20:41.156
- [gasps] You did it, Pig!
You saved the day!

20:41.240 --> 20:46.119
{\an3}- Pig, welcome to the
Super Secret Science Society.

20:46.203 --> 20:48.455
- Thanks.
I'm so gonna join that.

20:48.538 --> 20:50.999
[grunting]

20:51.083 --> 20:52.918
[laughs evilly]

20:53.001 --> 20:57.631
Right after
I take over the world!

20:57.714 --> 20:59.341
[grunts]

20:59.424 --> 21:00.425
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:00.509 --> 21:02.094
- [babbles]

21:02.177 --> 21:05.180
- Way to go,
you Fruit Loop dingus.

21:05.263 --> 21:08.475
Now your other stupid friend
is smart.

21:08.558 --> 21:10.936
- But kind of impressive, hmm?

21:11.019 --> 21:14.648
{\an1}Maybe even Super-Secret-Science-
Society level impressive?

21:14.731 --> 21:17.359
No?
- No!

21:17.442 --> 21:20.737
- [grunts]
And why are you guys in a cage

21:20.821 --> 21:22.197
on a frying pan?

21:22.280 --> 21:23.949
{\an1}- It's Pig.
He's an evil genius.

21:24.032 --> 21:26.076
We need to stop him.
- He's right.

21:26.159 --> 21:28.537
I, Pig, who is now evil,

21:28.620 --> 21:31.790
{\an1}will take over the wo--
[belches]

21:31.873 --> 21:34.292
[electricity crackles]

21:34.376 --> 21:35.877
[both grunt]

21:35.961 --> 21:39.381
- [screams]
- [roaring]

21:39.464 --> 21:40.549
- Shi-ka chi-ka!

21:40.632 --> 21:41.883
<i>[victorious music]</i>

21:43.343 --> 21:44.928
- [grunts]

21:45.012 --> 21:47.931
- [hums]
- Hey, I'm me again.

21:48.015 --> 21:49.725
- [grunts]
[towel snaps]

21:49.808 --> 21:51.268
[soft clattering, lock clicks]

21:51.351 --> 21:52.477
[all grunt]

21:52.561 --> 21:54.312
And that's towel I do it.

21:54.396 --> 21:55.856
Pig Goat Banana Cricket

21:55.939 --> 21:59.234
Burgerstein's got meat
for brains again high-five.

22:01.028 --> 22:05.073
{\an8}[gentle acoustic guitar music]

22:05.157 --> 22:12.164
{\an8}♪ ♪

22:25.302 --> 22:27.763
{\an8}[whoopee cushion whistles]
